<!-- FAQ -->
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<div class="faq supporting-questions">
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Is 10mg of melatonin safe?</h3><p>For most adults, 10mg is safe for short-term use. However, sleep researchers generally recommend 0.5-5mg as an effective range. Higher doses don't always work better and can cause morning grogginess. Start with half a gummy (5mg) and only increase if needed.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Will melatonin gummies make me groggy in the morning?</h3><p>At 10mg, some people do experience morning grogginess, especially when first starting. Taking them earlier (45-60 minutes before bed instead of 30) and starting with a lower dose can help. The effect usually diminishes as your body adjusts.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Are these vegetarian?</h3><p>Yes — Natrol uses a pectin-based formula instead of gelatin, making these suitable for vegetarians. They're also free of synthetic dyes and artificial flavors.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Can I take melatonin every night?</h3><p>Melatonin is generally considered safe for nightly use in the short to medium term. However, it's best used as a tool for resetting your sleep schedule rather than a permanent nightly supplement. Consult your doctor if you plan to use it for more than a few months.</p></div>
</div>

